  <p>
    Sooner or later many septic owners face the big question: keep repairing the system they have, or
    replace it. It's the most consequential — and most expensive — decision in septic ownership, and
    it deserves a clear-eyed process rather than a snap judgment. The honest answer is that it
    depends, and the factors it depends on are ones you can understand and weigh.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/septic-repair-versus-system-replacement-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
  <ResourceImageSlot
    src={"/images/resources/septic-repair-versus-system-replacement-hero.webp"}
